{
  "38911": {
    "Oh. This is...<pc>Hello!  You have come to the right\nplace.  I'm here to discuss something\nwith you. Recently, rumors have been\n<br>\ncirculating that a terrifying monster,\nthe likes of which has never been seen\nbefore, appears at night in the\n<br>\nvillages around Glen. Even if we\nwanted to investigate the truth, our\ncountry is short of manpower.  I was\n<br>\nthinking of hiring someone to\ninvestigate. The monster was said to\nhave appeared in Lion Gate Village.  I\n<br>\nwant you to go and talk to the\nwitnesses there and ask them about the\nmonster. Of course, I have a reward\n<br>\nfor you.  Will you do me a favor?": ""
  },
  "38912": {
    "<if_woman><attr><feel_happy_lv1><end_attr>Oh, you'll take care of it!  That's\nwhat I'm talking about.<pc>Which.  A nice gal who can be relied\non in times of need!<else><attr><feel_happy_lv1><end_attr>Oh, you'll take care of it!  That's\nwhat I'm talking about.<pc>Which one?  A nice guy who can be\nrelied on in times of need!<endif>": ""
  },
  "38913": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>I appreciate your concern, but it\nseems that you are busy with other\nrequests. Please take care of that\n<br>\nfirst, and then talk to me again.": ""
  },
  "38914": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>Mmmm, that's a shame.<pc>I would have felt safe entrusting my\nwork to you. If you change your mind\nagain, please feel free to talk to me\n<br>\nanytime.": ""
  },
  "38915": {
    "oh!<pc>Hello!  Are you sure you want to\naccept my request? I'd like you to go\nto Lion Gate Village and ask for\n<br>\ninformation on a monster that's been\nsighted there.": ""
  },
  "38916": {
    "I want you to tell me more about the\nmysterious monster that appeared in\nLion Gate Village, including any\n<br>\ninformation you can get from local\nwitnesses.<open_irai><bw_break>": ""
  },
  "38917": {
    "<close_irai><pc>I know it may be too easy for some of\nyou, but please do me a favor!": ""
  },
  "38918": {
    "oh!<pc>Hello!  It seems the investigation is\nover.  Let's hear your report. Lemur's\nChalice!  And a monster is headed in\n<br>\nthe direction of this castle.  What in\nthe world is going on? As a matter of\nfact, the Lemur's Chalice has been\n<br>\nkept in our castle's treasury since\nthe last incident. I found out that\nuntil a few decades ago, it belonged\n<br>\nto a wealthy merchant who lived in the\nneighboring country of Gartlant. The\nmerchant's lineage is now extinct, but\n<br>\nhow could such a treasure have ended\nup in the possession of a monster in\nthe Becon Valley? Anyway, in the\n<br>\ninterest of friendship with Gartlant,\nthe chalice was to be a gift to the\nroyal family of Gartlant in the not-\n<br>\ntoo-distant future. We don't know who\nthis monster is, but now that we know\nwho is after it, we'll have to keep a\n<br>\nvery close watch on the treasury!\nWell~ I'm glad you investigated!  I\nwill return the favor as promised.\n<br>\n Now, please accept this!": ""
  },
  "38922": {
    "Minister Chigri has been entrusted\nwith the Lemur's Chalice.  I have\nnothing to say to you.": ""
  },
  "38920": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>Eidos-sama doesn't listen to me at\nall, no matter how much I try to stop\nhim. Oh. Thanks to him, Minister\n<br>\nChigri gave me a hard time.": ""
  },
  "38926": {
    "Oh-ho!  I am the only scholar here at\nGlen Castle who studies history. Ogres\nare not very particular about the\n<br>\npast, you know. I'm afraid he doesn't\nunderstand the value of what I'm\ndoing.  It's a shame.": ""
  },
  "38927": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv2><end_attr>I have been ordered by the Minister to\nsearch the records for a man named\nSwordmaster Oren. However, I can't\n<br>\nfind the name of such a person\nanywhere in the castle's history\nbooks. Speaking of which, I've asked\n<br>\nthe Minister to find someone to help\nme with this investigation, but he\ncan't seem to find anyone, can he? It\n<br>\ncan't be helped. If you still haven't\nheard from him after waiting for a\nwhile, please go to the Minister and\n<br>\nask him about his helpers.": ""
  },
  "38928": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv1><end_attr>oh!<pc>Hello.  You have come to the right\nplace.  Actually, I'd like to discuss\nsomething with you. About the Lemur's\n<br>\nChalice the other day.  I'm still not\nconvinced by the behavior of Mr.\nEidos. Anyway, in order to find out\n<br>\nthe truth, I'm having the scholars of\nthe castle investigate Swordmaster\nOren. However, he seems to be having a\n<br>\nhard time, so Dandel the scholar asked\nme to find someone to help him out.\nDandel is in the servants' room on the\n<br>\nfirst floor, so if he is free, please\nhelp him.": ""
  },
  "38929": {
    "Oh-ho!  Perhaps the help I asked for\nfrom the Minister has arrived? I am\nThwarthog Danderu, the only historian\n<br>\nhere at Glen Castle. I was ordered by\nthe Minister to look into the records\nof Swordmaster Oren, but I can't find\n<br>\nhis name anywhere in the castle's\nhistory books. In fact, the history of\nGlen Castle was moved to a cave during\n<br>\nthe war to protect it from burning\ndown, and some of it remains there to\nthis day. I want you to go to that\n<br>\ncave and find the history book that\nstill contains Oren's writings. The\ncave is in the northwestern part of\n<br>\nthe Landonfoot region.  Will you do me\na favor?": ""
  },
  "38930": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv2><end_attr>Whoa-ho! Can you do it?  Now, please\ngo find a book called Glen History\nVol. 47. The history books before and\n<br>\nafter it indicate that Swordmaster\nOren appeared during that time period.\n Please, I'm counting on you!": ""
  },
  "38931": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>Noooo...!  I appreciate your kindness,\nbut it's not possible. If you are\nwilling to accept my offer, please\n<br>\nfirst solve that mountain of requests\nbefore you accept my offer.": ""
  },
  "38932": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>Noooooo! I thought you were the one\nwho was asked by the Minister to come\nhere, but it seems I was mistaken.": ""
  },
  "38933": {
    "Oh-ho!   So you are the one who came\nto help us at the minister's request,\nare you? In that case, I want you to\n<br>\ngo to the cave where the history book\nof Glen Castle was moved and find the\nhistory book that mentions Oren. The\n<br>\ncave is in the northwest part of\nLandonfoot.  Will you do me a favor?": ""
  },
  "38934": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv1><end_attr>I've been trying to find out more\nabout Swordmaster Oren from the castle\nscholars, but they seem to be having a\n<br>\nhard time. The scholar, Dandel, has\nasked me to find someone to help him.\nDandel is in the servants' room on the\n<br>\nfirst floor, so if he is free, please\nhelp him.": ""
  },
  "38935": {
    "Go to the northwest cave in the\nLandonfoot region and find the book\nGlen History Vol. 47.<open_irai><bw_break>": ""
  },
  "38936": {
    "<close_irai>From the history books before and\nafter, it is believed that Swordmaster\nOren appeared during that time period.\n<br>\n Please, I beg you!": ""
  },
  "38937": {
    "Dandel is an unusually intelligent\nOgre man, and above all, a serious man\nwho takes everything he does\n<br>\nseriously. If he can't find him, then\nSwordmaster Oren must not be mentioned\nin the castle's history books.": ""
  },
  "38938": {
    "Oh-ho! What you have in your hand is\nexactly Glen History Vol. 47!\n Quickly, hand it over.": ""
  },
  "38939": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv2><end_attr>Don't be so mean, please, please,\nplease!": ""
  },
  "38940": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv2><end_attr>Ho ho! Thank you very much.  Now I can\nproceed with my research on\nSwordmaster Oren!": ""
  },
  "39006": {
    "Would you give Glen History Vol. 47 to\nDundell?<yesno><case 1><break><case 2><close><case_cancel><close><case_end>": ""
  },
  "39007": {
    "<pc>gave Dundell a copy of Glen History\nVol. 47!": ""
  },
  "38943": {
    "oh!<pc>Hello.  How is your search for the\nhistory book that Dandel asked you to\nfind going?<yesno><break>": ""
  },
  "38944": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv1><end_attr>Hohoho. That's what I'm talking about.<pc>Which one?  I can look for a history\nbook before breakfast, I guess.  If\nthat's the case, please deliver them\n<br>\nquickly.": ""
  },
  "38945": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv2><end_attr>Mm-hmm.<pc>But who can't find him?  Who the hell\nis this Swordmaster Oren?": ""
  },
  "38948": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv1><end_attr>I've been ordered by the Minister to\nfind out how to talk to a wraith like\nSwordmaster Oren. But I'm not an\n<br>\nexpert in occult matters, so I'm\nhaving a hard time.": ""
  },
  "38949": {
    "I am relieved that I was able to\nfulfill the Minister's request. After\nall, I feel at home with a history\n<br>\nbook open.  I have had enough of the\noccult.": ""
  },
  "38950": {
    "oh!<pc>Hello.  You have come to the right\nplace. I've come to realize that I\ncan't know the truth about Oren or\n<br>\nEidos's thoughts just by looking\nthings up in a book. I have decided to\ntalk to Swordmaster Oren, who is at\n<br>\nthe center of the case. So, I'm having\nDandel, the scholar, look into ways to\ncommunicate with Oren. If you find a\n<br>\ngood way, please let me know.<pc>I was just about to ask for your\ncooperation.": ""
  },
  "38951": {
    "oh!<pc>Sir.  Are you sure you're ready to\naccept my request? Let me ask you\nagain.  Please.<%sEV_QUE_NAME0>and get me the Requiem Candle. Then go\nto the Swordsman Mound in the depths\nof Becon Valley and light the candle.\n<br>\nTalk to Swordmaster Oren and find out\nwhy he is seeking Lemur's Chalice!\nOren and Mr. Eidos have a close\n<br>\nconnection to this matter.<pc>I think it is only by which that we\nwill be able to achieve our goal.": ""
  },
  "38952": {
    "<if_woman><attr><feel_happy_lv1><end_attr>Oh, you'll take care of it!  That's\nwhat I'm talking about.<pc>Which.  A nice gal who can be relied\non in times of need! Well then, please\ndo me a favor.<%sEV_QUE_NAME0>is supposed to live in Calsadora\nVolcano in Dwachakka Continent!<else><attr><feel_happy_lv1><end_attr>Oh, you'll take care of it!  That's\nwhat I'm talking about.<pc>Which.  A nice guy who can be relied\non in times of need! I'll be counting\non you.<%sEV_QUE_NAME0>is supposed to live in Calsadora\nVolcano in Dwachakka Continent!<endif>": ""
  },
  "38953": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>I appreciate your concern, but it\nseems that you are busy with other\nrequests. Please take care of that\n<br>\nfirst, and then talk to me again.": ""
  },
  "38954": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>Mmmm, that's a shame.<pc>I would have felt safe entrusting my\nwork to you. If you change your mind\nagain, please feel free to talk to me\n<br>\nanytime.": ""
  },
  "38955": {
    "Calsadora Volcano, Dwachakka Continent\n A vicious monster<%sEV_QUE_NAME0>Go and get the Requiem Candle.<open_irai><bw_break>": ""
  },
  "38956": {
    "Then go to the Swordsman Mound in the\ndepths of Becon Valley and light the\ncandle. Talk to Swordmaster Oren and\n<br>\nfind out why he wants Lemur's Chalice!<bw_break>": ""
  },
  "38957": {
    "<close_irai>This case has a history with both Oren and Mr Eidos\n We have a close relationship<pc>I think it is only by which that we\nwill be able to achieve our goal.": ""
  },
  "38958": {
    "Oh, you received Requiem Candles right\naway, didn't you?  As one would\nexpect.<pc>Well then, at last! Well, next, we\nwill finally go to Becon Valley to\nface Swordmaster Oren.<open_irai><bw_break>": ""
  },
  "38959": {
    "Go use Requiem Candle to bring Oren to\nhis senses and ask him why he wants\nLemur's Chalice.<bw_break>": ""
  },
  "38960": {
    "<close_irai>This case has a history with both Oren and Mr Eidos\n We have a close relationship<pc>I think it is only by which that we\nwill be able to achieve our goal.": ""
  },
  "38961": {
    "Oh. You're back.<pc>Who.  So you were able to get\nSwordmaster Oren to tell you about\nLemur's Chalice? Oh my..!  Once again,\n<br>\nEidos-sama shows up and says such a\nthing? Hmmm. If Eidos-sama himself is\nwilling to tell us, then we have no\n<br>\nchoice.  I shall wait until then. Ah.\nOf course.<pc>We'll make sure you get your money's\nworth.  Now, please receive this.": ""
  },
  "38962": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv2><end_attr>However, from what I have heard about\nEidos and his friends, it seems that\nthey have known each other for a long\n<br>\ntime. A big villain who has been\nerased from history's stage and a wise\nman who is well-known throughout the\n<br>\nworld. What brought them together?\n It's a very interesting question,\nisn't it?": ""
  },
  "38966": {
    "oh!<pc>Hello.  You have come to the right\nplace. I haven't heard a word from Mr.\nEidos since the other day. It's about\n<br>\ntime.<pc>I was thinking of asking one of them\nto come and check on you.": ""
  },
  "38967": {
    "Now that I've heard all this, I want\nto see what Oren is going to do until\nthe end.<pc>Hello.  Let me ask you one more time.\nWill you please go to Sky Lake in the\nLandon Mountains, witness Oren's deed,\n<br>\nand report back to me how it went?": ""
  },
  "38968": {
    "<attr><feel_angry_lv1><end_attr>Oh, you'll take care of it?  I knew\nit!<pc>I am curious to see how this will turn\nout. That's why I can leave it to you.\n Then, I'll be counting on you to take\n<br>\ncare of it!": ""
  },
  "38969": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>I appreciate your concern, but it\nseems that you are busy with other\nrequests. Please take care of that\n<br>\nfirst, and then talk to me again.": ""
  },
  "38970": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>What a pity.  I can only entrust this\ncase to<pc>I would not have it any other way. If\nyou change your mind, please talk to\nme immediately.": ""
  },
  "38971": {
    "Eidos was here, but he left without\nsaying a word to me. Kooky.  As usual,\nyou don't even think of kings as\n<br>\nkings.  As expected of the great sage\nEidos.": ""
  },
  "38972": {
    "I want you to go to Sky Lake in the\nLandon Mountains, assess what Oren is\ndoing, and report back to me.<open_irai><bw_break>": ""
  },
  "38973": {
    "<close_irai>Now that I know so much about it, I'm\nnot satisfied with not seeing it\nthrough to the end.<pc>I'm sure all of you feel the same way.\n That's why we can leave it to you.": ""
  },
  "39073": {
    "<pc>told Minister Chigri about the events\nat Sky Lake.": ""
  },
  "38974": {
    "<attr><feel_angry_lv1><end_attr>I've been waiting for you.  So, what\nhappened at Sky Lake?  Please tell me\nmore about it.": ""
  },
  "38975": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv2><end_attr>I see.  It seems that Mr. Eidos has\nnot told us everything yet. Well,\nanyway, thank you for your hard work.\n<br>\n Here is a small token of our\nappreciation.  Please accept it.": ""
  },
  "38976": {
    "Did Mr. Eidos say that we will talk\nabout Oren another time? If so, I will\nbelieve him and wait for now.  He\n<br>\nwould never lie to us.": ""
  },
  "38980": {
    "I was told by the Minister that\nSwordmaster Oren was not, in fact, the\nbad guy that the history books said he\n<br>\nwas, but a very unhappy man. I think\nit is the great taste of historical\nstudies that such an unexpected fact\n<br>\nis revealed. Yes, yes.": ""
  },
  "38981": {
    "oh!<pc>Hello.  You've come to the right\nplace. We've tracked down Oren, who\nhad been missing since we lost him at\n<br>\nSky Lake! A soldier patrolling the\nBecon Valley area reported that Oren\nhad apparently returned to the valley.<pc>Hello. Could you continue from last\ntime to see what Oren is doing and\nreport back to us on how it's going?": ""
  },
  "38982": {
    "<attr><feel_angry_lv1><end_attr>Oh, you'll take me on?  I'll stay with\nyou until the end! I'll stay with you\nto the end!<pc>I can feel the spirit of the \"spirit\nof the world\".": ""
  },
  "38983": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>I appreciate your concern, but it\nseems that you are busy with other\nrequests. Please take care of that\n<br>\nfirst, and then talk to me again.": ""
  },
  "38984": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>What a pity.  I can only entrust this\ncase to<pc>I would not have it any other way. If\nyou change your mind, please talk to\nme immediately.": ""
  },
  "38985": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv2><end_attr>Eidos was here again, but he left\nwithout saying a word to me. Hmmm. I'm\na little rusty, as expected, since\n<br>\nI've been completely treated as if I\nwere air.": ""
  },
  "38986": {
    "Oren, who had been missing since the\nincident at Sky Lake, was reported to\nhave returned to Becon Valley.<pc>Please, please, please.  Please go\ndeep into the Becon Valley and see how\nOren is doing.<open_irai><bw_break>": ""
  },
  "38987": {
    "<close_irai>But I didn't expect Eidos-sama to\ninsist on going with us.  I have a\nfeeling that we are finally at the end\n<br>\nof the process.": ""
  },
  "39074": {
    "<pc>gave Minister Chigri the Lemur's\nChalice and told him about the events\nin the Becon Valley!": ""
  },
  "38988": {
    "<attr><feel_angry_lv1><end_attr>Oh, I've been waiting for you.  So,\nwhat happened this time?  Please tell\nme, please.": ""
  },
  "38989": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv2><end_attr>How is that possible?  Eidos-sama has\nbeen suffering for a long time over\nhis friend Oren, hasn't he? Anyway,\n<br>\nthis series of incidents concerning\nLemur's Chalice has finally been\nresolved. Thank you very much for your\n<br>\npatience with my selfishness.  Now,\nplease receive this in return.": ""
  },
  "38991": {
    "It seems that the matter of Lemur's\nChalice has been settled. The\nminister's long-suffering expression\n<br>\nhas finally returned to normal.  Let\nme also thank you.": ""
  },
  "38992": {
    "Whoa! This is...<pc>Dear Sir or Madam, I am currently\nworking on a new history book.  I am\ncurrently working on the concept of\n<br>\nwriting a new history book. I will\nsurely let the world know the truth\nabout the tragic sword saint Oren!": ""
  },
  "38993": {
    "The Lemur's Chalice, which you\nretrieved for me, rests in the\ntreasury of Glen Castle. Now that I\n<br>\nknow of the tragedy in Oren, I\nhesitate to give it as a gift, even if\nit is for the sake of friendship with\n<br>\nthe royal family of Gartlant. I would\nlike to discuss the matter with you\nwhen Eidos comes to visit.": ""
  },
  "68428": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv1><end_attr>Welcome to the guild.  I'm Rasedo, the\nguildmaster of this Weaponsmith Guild.\nWhat's your name?<pc>I see.  That's quite a flowery name.\n I think you'd make a good weapons\nsmith! Weapons smithing is the art of\n<br>\nmaking swords, spears, axes, and other\ncool metal weapons with your own\nhands. Weaponsmith Guild distributes\n<br>\nthe weapons we make to stores all over\nthe world. That's right! We make most\nof the weapons sold in the world! You\n<br>\nare an adventurer, aren't you? There\nare some people like you who travel\nand hone their craftsmanship skills,\n<br>\nbut these days, all the craftsmen's\nguilds are very busy.  They don't seem\nto be hiring new craftsmen or doing\n<br>\nmuch business with individuals. As a\nguild, we can't help you, but since\nyou've come all this way, I'll tell\n<br>\nyou something good. In this world,\nthere is a special blacksmith's stand\ncalled the Wonderful Blacksmith's\n<br>\nStand. Anyone with a recipe and the\nright materials can make all sorts of\nequipment. If you receive one, you\n<br>\nwill be Drang.  You won't have to go\nto the store to buy new equipment!\nWell, you'll have to prepare the\n<br>\nrecipe and materials yourself. If\nthat's too much of a hassle, you can\nalways buy equipment from the store!": ""
  },
  "205748": {
    "What? Where is Golanzo? Well, that's\nwhat the new guy's called.  He should\nbe in this back room.": ""
  },
  "53433": {
    "Are you a new trainee?  Mr. Ranbaba is\nhere to train Glen Castle's soldiers\nhard! Oh! Ranbaba is so nice!  I'm so\n<br>\nhappy that he takes my training so\nseriously!": ""
  },
  "53435": {
    "<attr><feel_normal_one><end_attr>This is Glen's special training\ngrounds!  I am the Instructor Ranbaba\nhere!  If you want to be strong, you\n<br>\nhave to train too! Young people these\ndays don't have enough spirit!  I\nwon't leave the future of Astoltia in\n<br>\nthe hands of such a loser!": ""
  },
  "34453": {
    "From the lifting bridge over the town\nto the massive castle, this place\nlooks like a fortress. Is that why?\n<br>\n The soldiers can't seem to relax even\nthough we're almost there.": ""
  },
  "34454": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv2><end_attr>I wonder if the king is all right.\n No, he's fine. A soldier's duty is to\nfight for his lord.  I'll do\n<br>\neverything I can for King Bagudo!": ""
  },
  "34455": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv1><end_attr>King Bagudo would not throw a man in\njail unless he is a very bad person.\n He believes that the essence of human\n<br>\nbeings is goodness. However, there\nhave been a lot of people thrown in\njail recently.": ""
  },
  "34456": {
    "Welcome to Glen Castle!  Our pride and\njoy, the Weaponsmith Guild, is located\nat the end of this passage. If you\n<br>\nhave come here to become a soldier,\nyou may speak with Nidolf in front of\nthe throne room on the second floor.": ""
  },
  "34457": {
    "Damn!  King Bagudo must have lost his\ntemper. Being imprisoned by the mild-\nmannered King Bagudo was a bit of a\n<br>\nstatus symbol for doing something so\nevil. But now he's throwing a good-\nnatured guy in jail who doesn't have a\n<br>\nshred of malice in him.  Oh, no, no,\nno! That's impossible!": ""
  },
  "34458": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv2><end_attr>I can't seem to get rid of fatigue.\n It's probably because the castle has\nbeen so busy these days.": ""
  },
  "34459": {
    "Beyond here is King Bagudo's throne\nroom.  The King will only see those\nwho wish to become our soldiers. As a\n<br>\nsoldier, you must have the Proof of\nAdulthood!  Those without the\nqualifications will be asked to leave.": ""
  },
  "34460": {
    "Beyond here is King Bagudo's throne\nroom.  He will only see those who wish\nto become our soldiers. Traveller. Do\n<br>\nyou wish to become one of our soldiers\nand receive the Black Key Emblem, the\nsymbol of Glen Castle's heroes?<yesno><break>": ""
  },
  "34461": {
    "Then walk away.": ""
  },
  "34462": {
    "In that case, let's see your Proof of\nAdulthood, shall we?  Mm. You\ncertainly seem to have it! Very\n<br>\nwell! Enter the Throne Room!  King\nBagudo will decide whether to hire you\nas a soldier of Glen. The king is\n<br>\nreceiving a guest now, so be quiet and\nwait inside.": ""
  },
  "34463": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv2><end_attr>Are you a new trainee?  Mr. Ranbaba is\nhere to train Glen Castle's soldiers\nhard! Oh! Ranbaba is so nice!  He\n<br>\ntakes his teaching so seriously!  I'm\nso happy!": ""
  },
  "34465": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>Few have the Proof of Adulthood, and\neven if they do, they cannot become\nsoldiers unless they are favored by\n<br>\nthe king. Even if you have it, you\ncan't become a soldier unless you are\nfavored by the king.": ""
  },
  "34466": {
    "I'll tell you now that you know, but\nthere's something wrong with the king.\nIf things continue as they are, there\n<br>\nwill indeed be some trouble in Ogreed\nContinent. If you are willing to help\nsave this country, please talk to\n<br>\nEidos and see if you can help! The inn\nwhere Eidos is staying is in the\nmiddle of the stairs in front of the\n<br>\ncastle, to the right.  I'm counting on\nyou!": ""
  },
  "34467": {
    "Lead Soldier Jidan told me about you.\n He told me that you would borrow some\nwisdom from Eidos and that you would\n<br>\ndo everything in your power to heal\nthe king. The Inn where Eidos is\nlocated is just past the stairs in\n<br>\nfront of the castle, on the right.\n I'm counting on you!": ""
  },
  "34468": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv2><end_attr>Lead Soldier Jidan caught me napping\nand gave me a good smack. By the way,\nthe straight left hand of the captain\n<br>\nwas just as destructive as in the\npast!  It was just as destructive as\nin the past!": ""
  },
  "34469": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>It seems that Lead Soldier Jidan was\nable to get you out of jail.  I'm\nsorry to have caused you so much\n<br>\ntrouble. The king's temper has flared\nup because he suffers from a terrible\nheadache.  Why is this happening to\n<br>\nonly the king? If you enter the Throne\nRoom, the King's health may\ndeteriorate again.  I am sorry, but I\n<br>\nmust ask you to leave.": ""
  },
  "34470": {
    "Since you are aware, I must tell you\nthat ever since his recovery from his\nrecent illness, there has been\n<br>\nsomething wrong with the king. King\nBagudo has refused to listen to his\norders to do anything, and he has even\n<br>\nordered that anyone who objects be\nthrown in jail and beheaded. Of\ncourse, through the efforts of Lead\n<br>\nSoldier Jidan and Minister Chigri,\nthose people were secretly saved. If\nthings continue as they are, things\n<br>\nwill get really bad.  If Eidos is\nright and the king can be restored to\nhis former self, I would like your\n<br>\nhelp.": ""
  },
  "34471": {
    "Have you had the pleasure of meeting\nwith Master Eidos?  How could a king\nbe so infested? We didn't think King\n<br>\nBagudo really wanted any of this, but\nnow we see the point. We will fight\nwith our lives anytime if that's what\n<br>\nthe king really wants!  But this time,\nplease, save the king!": ""
  },
  "34472": {
    "Oh, you!  Eidos told me all about you.\n You brought me the Droplet of Gloris,\ndid you not? Come, come into the\n<br>\nThrone Room.  Lead Soldier Jidan is\nwaiting for you.": ""
  },
  "34473": {
    "From the lifting bridge over the town\nto the massive castle structure, this\nplace looks like a fortress.": ""
  },
  "34474": {
    "It was demon miasma that made me lose\nmy mind.  I remember a long time ago,\nthere was an entity called \"miasma.\n<br>\nWhen demon miasma is in the air, a\ngreat darkness is creeping in. We must\nunite beyond our species to face it.\n<br>\n Let's use this life we have been\ngiven to live for the sake of the\nworld.": ""
  },
  "34475": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv1><end_attr>Word of the cancellation of the\nIrukuso with Gartlant seems to have\nspread quickly. I am sure the\n<br>\ntownspeople were hoping that the\nIrukuso would be cancelled.": ""
  },
  "34476": {
    "Even though he was acting strangely,\nLeader Soldier Jidan must have been\ndistressed to let the imprisoned man\n<br>\ngo against the order of his beloved\nking. Minister Chigri was also worried\nabout King Bagudo's headache and could\n<br>\nnot sleep at night. You saved not only\nKing Bagudo but many others and\nbrought peace to the world.  I thank\n<br>\nyou from the bottom of my heart. Thank\nyou!": ""
  },
  "34477": {
    "Welcome to Glen Castle!  It is thanks\nto you that peace has been restored to\nour land!  Thank you for saving our\n<br>\nking and our country!": ""
  },
  "34478": {
    "Heh.  King Bagudo was crazy, wasn't\nhe? It was strange to think that he\nwould throw even a good-natured person\n<br>\nwith no trace of malice into jail!": ""
  },
  "34479": {
    "The king has been restored to health.\n Thanks to you and Mr. Eidos.  I'm\ngrateful. But don't forget to thank\n<br>\nSage Malynn for getting rid of the\nnecklace.  Thanks to all of you, this\ncountry is saved.": ""
  },
  "34480": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv2><end_attr>King Bagudo's headache is gone and\nhe's back to his former mild-mannered\nself! That's great! I'm so glad!  Now\n<br>\nthat the king is better, we can rest\neasy.  This country will regain its\nformer brightness!": ""
  },
  "34481": {
    "Beyond this is King Bagudo's throne\nroom.  Our Hero<pc>I'm going to go to the throne room.\n You want to go into the Throne Room?<yesno><case 1><break><case 2><close><case_cancel><close><case_end>": ""
  },
  "41976": {
    "Very well! Please come in.": ""
  },
  "34483": {
    "I heard that Gartlant was not willing\nto accept Irukko's offer.  I wonder\nwhat is going on here?": ""
  },
  "34484": {
    "The king's headache was too painful to\nbear. We tried to soothe his heart by\nobeying his every command.  But we\n<br>\nwere wrong. If we had started the wars\nunder the king's displeasure, the\nconsequences would have been\n<br>\nunforgivable.  You saved us. I thank\nyou.": ""
  },
  "34485": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv2><end_attr>Thanks to you!  Thanks to you! I'm so\nglad I met you!  I'm so glad I met\nyou!  I am so glad to have met you!": ""
  },
  "34486": {
    "Sage Malynn never thought that the\ndemon miasma would torment the king\nlike that, even after he took off the\n<br>\nnecklace. With Mr. Eidos.<pc>I am glad that you came to our\ncountry.  Thank you very much!": ""
  }
}